</p></section><section id="GUID-92369981-F020-4E62-9707-58F93D054214" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p "> The mechanical properties of the ink pump tubes change within their lifetime. To guarantee a consistent ink flow, the software tunes the ink pump control by means of a flow correction factor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This factor can be positive or negative (depending on the current efficiency of the pump tube). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When replacing the pump tube, the lifetime counter of the pump tube needs to be reset. This will automatically reset the ink flow correction factor to 1. 
